well, Aileen and I were talking about this back in the day.  You know how Shakira's video for "Whenever, Wherever" features her rolling in the mud?  well, back then i was just like whateverer, she's weird....  music videos are weird.  little did i know what her next video would be like.  has anyone seen "La Tortura"?  This one features her literally spreading tar (yes, tar) all over her body.  What is up with that girl?!?!?!?

so it turns out the concert is NEXT saturday, so I can go to it.  and i didn't get my permit.  the stupid DMV didn't even let me take the test because i don't have an "acceptable" copy of my birth certificate......i have to get one certified from the county and blah blah blah......i hate the DMV.

just thought i would update, considering i haven't written in this thing for almost a month.  i've spent all my time on myspace.  spring break was way fun.  i learned to surf, which was cool, but i hurt my knee.  i can sympathize with you now wendy.  even though it's not a serious injury, knee injuries suck.  and i have a pretty bruise to show off too.  lol.

i'm so freaking busy the next week.  i have my permit test, three meets, STAR testing, AP test, SAT 2, an all day dance festival, and an orchestra concert that i can't go to.  

i'm kinda worried about my Spanish AP test.  i have been studying a lot, but i'm not doing too well on the practice tests.  hopefully *crosses fingers* i will get at least a three.  and good luck to everyone else taking AP tests and SAT's!!!!

so i had an ok weekend.  on friday and saturday i babysat, so i made mucho dinero.  lol.  then on saturday night i was at target with my mom, and i hear someone shout "there she is!"  i look over and there is tara and wendy.  they were to there to pick me up to see miss congeniality 2.

note:this is the first movie i have seen since meet the fockers, which i saw in january.  lol.  i don't really like going to the movie theater anymore because it is so expensive.  i'd rather just rent movies and only go to the theater for really good ones.

anyone, the movie was really good, as sequels go.  it was really funny.  also, i just finished watching the passion of the christ.  people, don't see it.  it is so sad and gruesome. i had to close my eyes for like ten minutes, and i was watching the edited version.  very touching though.

sorry-it's another angry entry.  just had to express my feelings.  it's actually pretty therapeutic.

to a certain someone-you piss me off.  frankly, my life would be a lot better without you in it.  i've been pretty damn happy for the past two months, and that's more than i can say about the months before that.  i don't care what you think about me, i just don't want people assuming or thinking things about me that aren't true.  as for my opinion on you, that's all based on facts.

i don't feel like updating.  but, let's see how many  comments i can get on one entry.  everyone comment!
p.s.  hit me up on my myspace.

so my vacation was good, i'm glad to be back though.  i missed everyone!  not really anything to write about.  oh yeah, this one guy in blink 182 has a really weird and ugly voice.  and the lead singer of oasis has a weird voice too, but i really like both bands.

AND i found this HILARIOUS picture of my brother with mabet and nick from senior grad night.  if it lets me i'll post it.  i'm still laughing.

so the past two days have been awesome.  thursday most of you have heard about, i won't go into detail here but feel free to ask me to spill all my juicy details of tara and alicia's ultimate day of fun.  lol.

yesterday was actually surprisingly fun taking the bus to valleyfair.  tara met us there later.  it was pretty fun except for the "white trash" guy.....i guess i should tell the story.

so the three of us were walking through the mall, and this guy stops us saying something about how he has to talk to thirty nice and pretty girls to become a dj or something rather.  then he has us come over and says he needs two minutes.  well, i thought we were just gonna have to sign something saying he talked to us or something, but next thing you know he takes out this brochure full of magazines that he wants us to buy.

well, tara says that she has to go the bathroom and leaves (smart girl) while laura decides she wants to get teen people.  well, she starts filling out the form and it turns out it's 16 bucks plus 8 dollars shipping and handling...wth?

well we told him that we didn't have enough money, but he knew i had 6 bucks.  he complained about how he only needed a few more points and that the last girl gave him like a hundred bucks.  he said he just wanted the six bucks and he would donate the rest to buy some kid's magazine.  so i gave it to him...i know-it was a mistake.  tara was pretty mad about it too lol.

well all in all these past two days have been awesome...hopefully today wil be too.

yesterday was soooooo much fun....laura and i are gonna be fashion designers!! lol.

so we brought out all our old clothes and tweaked them and made new stuff...it was so awesome.  we both have lots of cool clothes to wear when we go back to school.  we worked on that for a few hours, then went out to see meet the fockers with nick.  it was pretty funny.

and i just realized that he is turning 20 in 4 days....

so today this girl that i don't know ims me and says that she think my xanga is "wicked kewl"....it was all ok although a little weird until she starts talking about how there are perverts on the internet so she doesn't post her pic, and that for some reason she trusts me so she sent me her picture.  it just seemed a little weird considering we don't know each other.

then she started talking about how we are so alike and would probably be friends if we went to the same school, and that all her friends have big boobs so i would fit in.  that just weirded me out.  all in all she seems pretty nice though.

I don't hate a certain "Mrs.  Piggle Wiggle"  anymore.  I know only a couple of you know who this is, but I'd prefer not to write her name on here.  The sad thing is after all of these years of hate and despise.....all those feelings went away with these few simple words, "You look cute today."

Is it sad that I have denied a friendship with her for all of these years simply because of the childish and mean way she acted towards me in sixth grade, five years ago?  If I hadn't held a grudge on her, would we be friends today?

Well I guess I shouldn't venture to say we are friends now, but I really don't hate her.  I don't know why I ever did.  She really isn't mean, and my whole perception of her was based on a few measly comments she said to me five years ago.  Just had to get this off my chest....

so some of you might want to know why i am updating my livejournal at 6:30 in the morning.  in short, i woke up at 5:15 and couldn't get back to sleep, so what better to do than blog?

yesterday was pretty interesting.  short day, afterschool walked to tara's house.  listened to the song that SHE WROTE.  it's so good!  i'm so proud of you tara my up and coming artist!  i will definitely go to your shows and stuff when you get famous.

then had to walk back to school for tara's band practice....depressing as hell.  i hate being in the orchestra room when all the band geeks are there (no offense).  it was just sad that during vacation, all these people in band were at school to practice.....early.

then my mom drove laura and i to la salsa.  their burritos really are spicy!  it was kind of nasty.

after my cello lesson, i went back to the library with tara, laura, and nick to wait for dusty.  he never showed up.

an interesting thing happened there,  well i was leaning pretty far back in those  chairs, and it kinda fell.  as tara says, and i agree, it was funny until my head hit the table behind me.  really hard.  it hurt so bad.  well nick and tara were pretty worried that i had a concussion, so nick took his little flashlight and shined it into my pupils.  verdict:i didn't have a concussion.  but that didn't stop it from hurting like hell.

i seriously couldn't get up for like 5 minutes.  i was just sitting there on the ground.  nick was freaking me out cuz i was resting my head down cuz it hurt so much, and he's all like don't go to sleep you might not wake up.

of course when we went to downtown mountain view, tara and laura insisted on running across the street, which of course i couldn't do bc of my stupid head.

well now i guess it feels better.  i don't really have a headache anymore, but i have a pretty big bump on the back of my head.  everyone time it touches something it hurts.  i had to be pretty careful with my pillow.

that's pretty much all that happened yesterday.  i'm so excited for the weekend though!  and no homework!! yay!
